{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4b0aaeab-4f36-4637-a38a-a59fd9101f58","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing code, I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding:\n1. The `xmlns:vm` namespace import\n2. `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element\n\nEvery `{Binding}` in scope is now compiled — the XAML compiler resolves property names against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** for typos (e.g., `{Binding Themee}` → `CS0117`). To enforce this project-wide, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding warnings as errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the MAUI/Xamarin XAML compiler warning for unresolvable bindings. Promoting it to an error ensures no uncompiled or broken binding slips through CI.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `x:DataType` can be set on **any element**, not just the root — useful when a `DataTemplate` binds to a different type.\n- To opt out for one binding (e.g., a `BindingContext` assignment), use `x:DataType=\"\"` or `{Binding Source=...}`.\n- Compiled bindings also improve runtime performance by skipping reflection.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6020d59b-cc65-44df-8fae-f076e6c587bc","outputTokens":695},"id":"4a9afb2a-c0bf-48cb-8c7d-dfabd27c2e65","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:59:19.819Z","parentId":"9b76ec03-726b-43d6-a48c-ca1e8092030b"}
